comment: I /think/ 'mfad' is singular and 'fad' is plural? But it could be the other way around? the text is a little unclear
I /think/ 'mfad' is singular and 'fad' is plural? But it could be the other way around? the text is a little unclear
also used as honourable address for a man
also 'ma᷅', 'in connection with the name of the child', AC10(177)
glossed as "father caring for another's child"
